ce:section.ce:para:
The practical application of the ratiometric fluorescent probe (B-O-CDs) for the determination of tartrazine in food samples (orange juice, saffron tea bag, and jelly) was investigated using the standard addition approach. In short, different amounts of tartrazine were spiked in pre-prepared samples, and the associated fluorescence spectra were recorded in the optimal conditions (Fig. 7
                        ). As shown in Table 1
                        , the recovery values for tartrazine in the different matrices were in the range of 97.2–104.4 %. Additionally, the relative standard deviation (RSD, n = 3) for all the samples was lower than 3.5 %. The obtained results indicate the capability of B-O-CDs in the determination of tartrazine in food samples with high sensitivity and reproducibility. Moreover, the robustness of the method against various environmental conditions enables us to use this sensor for in situ applications.
